icient. No AI dependency.","test_description":"Use handler + real local persistent queue store with id uniqueness, submit same event ID twice, assert first accepted and second does not create another queue record.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"When the queue reports it is full, the handler returns 503 with a Retry-After header.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is error-contract mapping across modules (queue status -> HTTP status/header). Unit of mapper alone can miss wiring issues in handler response path. Integration-brake checks: no real OS/network/subprocess requirement in behavior text, no AI output dependency, no multi-agent chain; therefore keep Integration.","test_description":"Run handler in-process with queue dependency configured to return/full-error; send valid webhook and assert HTTP 503 plus Retry-After header and no downstream processing dispatch.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"The persistent queue actually enforces its configured capacity limit and rejects events that would exceed it.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Behavior targets queue component plus its persistence/config wiring, not just a pure algorithm. Need real local persistence path to catch enforcement bugs. System considered but rejected because behavior text does not require external network/subprocess/OS primitives beyond local storage module interaction. No AI dependency.","test_description":"Instantiate queue with real local persistence backend and explicit capacity N, enqueue N events successfully, attempt N+1 and assert deterministic rejection/error without corrupting stored queue state.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities